# Signup Flow Drops 38% of Users at Email Verification

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Visit signup page<br/>1,000 users] --> B[Enter email<br/>820]
    B --> C{Email valid?}
    C -- yes --> D[Receive verification email<br/>820]
    C -- no --> E[Show error<br/>0 lost — same step]
    D --> F[Click verification link<br/>510]
    F --> G[Set password<br/>495]
    G --> H[Account created<br/>490]
```

Source: signup funnel telemetry, week of 2026-03-24. Numbers are user counts at each
step. Largest drop: between "Receive verification email" and "Click verification link"
(38% of remaining funnel).

Use this format for surfaces that auto-render mermaid (GitHub, GitLab, Notion,
Obsidian, recent VS Code). For surfaces that do not (Slack, email, plain chat,
generic tickets), emit the `mermaid-flowchart.html.tmpl` variant instead.
